			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Senior UK politician says MI5 covered up paedophile rings to blackmail politician
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1796414">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyril_Smith" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyril_Smith</a><br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<br />
In later years his popularity was considerably marred by the allegation that he had been involved in a cover-up of a health risk at a local asbestos factory. In 2008, there were calls for Smith to be stripped of his knighthood after it was revealed that he had asked the asbestos company Turner &amp; Newall to prepare a speech for him in 1981, in which he declared: &quot;The public at large are not at risk&quot;. It was later revealed that Smith owned 1,300 shares in the company. In 2008 he said that 4,000 asbestos-related deaths a year in the UK was &quot;relatively low&quot;.[2]<br />
<br />
In 2012, following allegations of child abuse, the Crown Prosecution Service formally admitted Smith should have been charged with the sexual abuse of boys during his lifetime. Greater Manchester Police said the boys &quot;were victims of physical and sexual abuse&quot; by Smith.[3][4] In November 2012, GMP Assistant Chief Constable Steve Heywood said there was &quot;overwhelming evidence&quot; that young boys were sexually and physically abused by Smith<br />
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elm_Guest_House_child_abuse_scandal" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elm_Gue..._abuse_scandal</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Wales_child_abuse_scandal" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_W..._abuse_scandal</a><br />
<br />
<br />
Westminster should be burned to the ground, pissed on and left as a lesson for history like the Hiroshima Dome but for a much damn different reason.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
